60 // This duplicates the formula.
61 // It removes tokens preceeded by the special marker.
62 
63 auto Math::duplicate(bool nomath) const -> subtypes {
64  subtypes k = math_data.find_math_location(type, sname);
65  Math & cp = math_data.get_list(k);
66  int sp = 0, sm = 0;
67  bool skipping = false;
68  bool skip_next = false;
69  auto C = value.begin();
70  auto E = value.end();
71  while (C != E) {
72  skip_next = skipping;
73  if (C->get_cmd() == nomath_cmd) {
74  int s = C->get_chr();
75  ++C;
76  if (C == E) break;
77  if (s == 0)
78  skip_next = nomath;
79  else if (s == 1)
80  skip_next = !nomath;
81  else {
82  if (s == 2)
83  sp++;
84  else if (s == 3) {
85  if (sp > 0) sp--;
86  sm++;
87  } else if (s == 4) {
88  if (sm > 0) sm--;
89  } else {
90  sp = sm = 0;
91  } // should not happen, clear the stack
92  skipping = false;
93  if (sp > 0 && nomath) skipping = true;
94  if (sm > 0 && !nomath) skipping = true;
95  skip_next = skipping;
96  }
97  }
98  if (skip_next) {
99  } else if (C->get_cmd() == math_list_cmd) {
100  Math & v = C->get_list();
101  subtypes k1 = v.duplicate(nomath);
102  cp.push_back_list(k1, C->get_lcmd());
103  } else if (C->get_cmd() == special_math_cmd) {
104  Math & v = C->get_list();
105  subtypes k1 = v.duplicate(nomath);
106  cp.push_back(CmdChr(special_math_cmd, k1), C->get_font());
107  } else
108  cp.push_back(*C);
109  ++C;
110  }
111  return k;
112 }

124 // Three functions that add something to the trace.
125 // We want spaces line this: \frac\pi x\bar\alpha
126 
127 void math_ns::add_to_trace(Token T) {
128  old_need = trace_needs_space;
129  old_pos = Trace.size();
130  auto x = T.val;
131  if (trace_needs_space && T.cmd_val() == letter_catcode) Trace.push_back(' ');
132  if (T.is_a_char() && T.char_val() == '\n')
133  Trace.push_back("^^J");
134  else
135  Trace.push_back(T);
136  trace_needs_space = false;
137  if (x >= single_offset) trace_needs_space = true;
138 }

155 auto tralics_ns::math_env_name(subtypes chr) -> String {
156  switch (chr) {
157  case eqnarray_code: return "endeqnarray";
158  case eqnarray_star_code: return "endeqnarray*";
159  case Beqnarray_code: return "endBeqnarray";
160  case Beqnarray_star_code: return "endBeqnarray*";
161  case multline_code: return "endmultline";
162  case multline_star_code: return "endmultline*";
163  case gather_code: return "endgather";
164  case gather_star_code: return "endgather*";
165  case equation_code: return "endequation";
166  case equation_star_code: return "endequation*";
167  case align_code: return "endalign";
168  case align_star_code: return "endalign*";
169  case flalign_code: return "endflalign";
170  case flalign_star_code: return "endflalign*";
171  case alignat_code: return "endalignat";
172  case alignat_star_code: return "endalignat*";
173  case xalignat_code: return "endxalignat";
174  case xalignat_star_code: return "endxalignat*";
175  case xxalignat_code: return "endxxalignat";
176  case xxalignat_star_code:
177  return "endxxalignat*";
178  // special math
179  case math_code: return "endmath";
180  case displaymath_code:
181  return "enddisplaymath";
182  // inner math
183  case array_code: return "endarray";
184  case split_code: return "endsplit";
185  case aligned_code: return "endaligned";
186  case gathered_code: return "endgathered";
187  case matrix_code: return "endmatrix";
188  case bordermatrix_code: return "endbordermatrix "; // space ?
189  case matrixb_code: return "endbmatrix";
190  case matrixB_code: return "endBmatrix";
191  case matrixp_code: return "endpmatrix";
192  case matrixV_code: return "endVmatrix";
193  case matrixv_code:
194  return "endvmatrix";
195  // special
196  case mbox_S_code: return "endmbox";
197  case text_S_code: return "endtext";
198  case fbox_S_code: return "endfbox";
199  case hbox_S_code: return "endhbox";
200  default: return nullptr;
201  }
202 }

204 // symbolic properties
205 // 1 means: external (otherwise internal)
206 // 2 means: one equation number (implies 1)
207 // 4 means: one equation number per row (implies 1)
208 // 8 means: array
209 // 16 has an optional ignored arg
210 // 32 has an required ignored
211 
212 auto tralics_ns::math_env_props(subtypes chr) -> int {
213  switch (chr) {
214  case eqnarray_code: return 1 + 4 + 8;
215  case eqnarray_star_code: return 1 + 8;
216  case Beqnarray_code: return 1 + 4 + 8;
217  case Beqnarray_star_code: return 1 + 8;
218  case multline_code: return 1 + 2 + 8;
219  case multline_star_code: return 1 + 8;
220  case gather_code: return 1 + 4 + 8;
221  case gather_star_code: return 1 + 8;
222  case equation_code: return 1 + 2;
223  case equation_star_code: return 1;
224  case align_code: return 1 + 4 + 8;
225  case align_star_code: return 1 + 8;
226  case flalign_code: return 1 + 4 + 8;
227  case flalign_star_code: return 1 + 8;
228  case alignat_code: return 1 + 4 + 8 + 32;
229  case alignat_star_code: return 1 + 8 + 32;
230  case xalignat_code: return 1 + 4 + 8 + 32;
231  case xalignat_star_code: return 1 + 8 + 32;
232  case xxalignat_code: return 1 + 4 + 8 + 32;
233  case xxalignat_star_code: return 1 + 8 + 32;
234  case math_code: return 1;
235  case displaymath_code: return 1;
236  case array_code: return 8;
237  case split_code: return 8;
238  case aligned_code: return 8 + 16;
239  case gathered_code: return 8 + 16;
240  case matrix_code: return 8;
241  case bordermatrix_code: return 8;
242  case matrixb_code: return 8;
243  case matrixB_code: return 8;
244  case matrixp_code: return 8;
245  case matrixV_code: return 8;
246  case matrixv_code: return 8;
247  default: return 0;
248  }
249 }

251 // Name of a math object. In a previous version, the name was a character string.
252 // Now it is a subtype. The name has the form "endmath" and we remove the prefix
253 auto Math::get_name() const -> String {
254  subtypes w = get_sname();
255  if (w == nomathenv_code) return "";
256  String S = tralics_ns::math_env_name(w);
257  if (S != nullptr) return S + 3;
258  return "bad";
259 }

263 // Interprets the meta data of the list
264 auto operator<<(std::ostream &X, math_list_type y) -> std::ostream & {
265  switch (y) {
266  case invalid_cd: X << "Invalid list"; break;
267  case math_open_cd: X << "simple group"; break;
268  case math_dollar_cd: X << "Inline formula"; break;
269  case math_ddollar_cd: X << "Display formula"; break;
270  case math_env_cd: X << "Environment"; break;
271  case math_LR_cd: X << "Left/right pair"; break;
272  case math_hbox_cd: X << "Hbox"; break;
273  case math_argument_cd: X << "Argument"; break;
274  default: {
275  CmdChr x(special_math_cmd, math_to_sub(y));
276  String w = x.name();
277  if (w != nullptr)
278  X << "Argument list for \\" << w;
279  else
280  X << "impossible " << int(y);
281  break;
282  }
283  }
284  return X;
285 }

315 // Prints a list into the Trace buffer
316 void Math::print() const {
317  Trace << "{" << type;
318  if (sname == nomathenv_code)
319  Trace << "\n";
320  else
321  Trace << " name= " << get_name() << "\n";
322  if (empty())
323  Trace << "empty";
324  else {
325  int k = 0;
326  auto C = value.begin();
327  auto E = value.end();
328  while (C != E) {
329  k++;
330  Trace << k << " ";
331  C->print();
332  ++C;
333  }
334  }
335  Trace << "}\n";
336 }

338 // This prints a math element
339 void MathElt::print() const {
340  int cmd = get_cmd();
341  int chr = get_chr();
342  if (cmd == nomath_cmd) {
343  Trace << "only for " << (chr == zero_code ? "math\n" : "nomath\n");
344  return;
345  }
346  Trace << "ME " << cmd << " - ";
347  if (32 < chr && chr < 128)
348  Trace << "char " << uchar(chr);
349  else
350  Trace << chr;
351  // is this secure ???
352  // if(cmd>16) Trace << " - " << Token(get_font());
353  if (cmd == mathfont_cmd || is_m_font(symcodes(cmd)))
354  Trace << " - " << Token(get_font()) << "\n";
355  else
356  Trace << " - " << int(get_font()) << "\n";
357  if (cmd == math_list_cmd || cmd == special_math_cmd) get_list().print(); // recurse
358 }

363 // General fence around val.
364 auto MathDataP::make_mfenced(int open, int close, Xml *val) -> Xml * {
365  Xml *res = new Xml(cst_mfenced, nullptr);
366  res->add_att(Istring(np_close), xml_lr_ptable[close]);
367  res->add_att(Istring(np_open), xml_lr_ptable[open]);
368  bool single_elt = val->size() == 1;
369  if (the_names[np_separator] == the_names[cst_mrow]) {
370  if (!single_elt) val = new Xml(cst_mrow, val);
371  } else if (the_names[np_separator].empty() && single_elt) {
372  } else
373  res->add_att(cst_separators, np_separator);
374  res->add_tmp(val);
375  return res;
376 }

378 // This adds a style element above res.
379 auto MathDataP::add_style(int lvl, Xml *res) -> Xml * {
380  if (lvl < 0) return res; // special case
381  res = new Xml(cst_mstyle, res);
382  if (lvl == 0) {
383  res->add_att(cst_displaystyle, np_true);
384  res->add_att(cst_scriptlevel, cst_dig0);
385  } else {
386  res->add_att(cst_displaystyle, np_false);
387  res->add_att(cst_scriptlevel, name_positions(cst_dig0 + lvl - 1));
388  }
389  return res;
390 }

392 // Implements \cellattribute
393 void MathHelper::add_attribute(Istring a, Istring b, subtypes c) {
394  Xid w;
395  if (c == cell_attribute_code)
396  w = cur_cell_id;
397  else if (c == row_attribute_code)

399  else if (c == table_attribute_code)

402  w = cur_math_id;

404  w = cur_formula_id;
405  else
406  return;
407  w.add_attribute(a, b, true);
408 }

412 // Adds a label to the formula X
413 void Parser::add_math_label(Xml *res) {
414  if (cmi.get_eqnum_status() == 1) {
415  cmi.ml_last_pass(tracing_math());
416  if (the_tag.empty()) return;
417  }
418  Istring my_id = the_main->SH.next_label_id();
419  if (the_tag.empty()) {
420  static int mid = 0;
421  mid++;
422  math_buffer << bf_reset << "mid" << mid;
423  the_tag = math_buffer.to_string();
424  }
425  the_stack.create_new_anchor(res->get_id(), my_id, Istring(the_tag));
426  const std::string &label = cmi.get_label_val();
427  if (!label.empty()) create_label(label, my_id);
428 }

463 void MathDataP::realloc_list() {

542 // Returns the next style in the list D,T, S, SS.
543 // D and T give S, S gives SS, and SS gives SS.
544 // Knuth uses: 2*(x/4)+1+1 for sub, 2*(x/4)+1+ (x mod2) for sub
545 auto math_ns::next_math_style(math_style x) -> math_style {
546  switch (x) {
547  case ms_T:
548  case ms_D: return ms_S;
549  default: return ms_SS;
550  }
551 }
552 
553 // Knuth uses: x+2-2*(x/6) for numerator x*(x/2)+1+2-2*(x/6) for denominator
554 auto math_ns::next_frac_style(math_style x) -> math_style {
555  switch (x) {
556  case ms_D: return ms_T;
557  case ms_T: return ms_S;
558  default: return ms_SS;
559  }
560 }
561 
562 // Takes the code of a command like \textstyle, returns ms_T
563 auto math_ns::style_level(subtypes tt) -> math_style {
564  if (tt == displaystyle_code) return ms_D;
565  if (tt == textstyle_code) return ms_T;
566  if (tt == scriptstyle_code) return ms_S;
567  if (tt == scriptscriptstyle_code) return ms_SS;
568  return ms_T;
569 }

588 // This is called before every math formula.
589 void MathHelper::reset(bool dual) {
590  free_list = nullptr;
591  current_mode = false;
592  pos_att = cst_dig0;
593  seen_label = false;
594  warned_label = false;
595  label_val = "";
596  tag_list = TokenList();
597  is_tag_starred = false;
598  math_env_ctr = 0;
599  all_env_ctr = 0;
600  cur_math_id = the_main->the_stack->next_xid(nullptr);
601  cur_formula_id = the_main->the_stack->next_xid(nullptr);
602  if (dual)

685 // This is done to the main math list U when we start reading a formula.
686 
687 // Second argument is nomathenv_code if a dollar has been read,
688 // the subtype of the token otherwise;
689 // Note: \( and \[ expand to $$, in all other cases we have an environment
690 // for instance \begin{math} or \begin{equation}. We compute and insert
691 // the name of the environment.
692 // Sets and returns the inline/non-inline flag
693 
694 auto Parser::start_scan_math(Math &u, subtypes type) -> bool {
695  u.set_name(type);
696  if (type == nomathenv_code) { // case of $...
697  add_to_trace(cur_tok);
698  get_token(); // no expansion
699  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == 3) {
700  add_to_trace(cur_tok);
701  u.set_display_type();
702  return false;
703  }
704  if (cur_tok != hash_table.relax_token) back_input();
705  u.set_nondisplay_type();
706  return true;
707  }
708  // case of \begin{...}
709  u.set_type(math_env_cd);
710  if ((math_env_props(type) & 1) == 0) {
711  math_buffer << bf_reset;
712  math_buffer << "Environment " << u.get_name() << " should only be used in math mode";
713  parse_error(math_buffer.c_str());
714  }
715  if ((math_env_props(type) & 16) != 0) ignore_optarg();
716  if ((math_env_props(type) & 32) != 0) read_arg();
717  return type == math_code;
718 }

732 // This piece of code is executed when the math formula has been read
733 // and translated. If the formula is inline, we execute \leavevmode
734 // Otherwise, it is a display math formula, we finish the current paragraph
735 // and look at the next (expanded) token. If it is no \par, we insert
736 // a \noindent.
737 void Parser::after_math(bool is_inline) {
738  cmi.finish_math_mem();
739  if (is_inline)
740  leave_v_mode();
741  else if (the_stack.is_frame(np_fbox))
742  return;
743  else {
744  bool w = the_stack.in_h_mode() || the_stack.in_v_mode();
745  leave_h_mode();
746  if (the_main->interactive_math) return; // no need to be subtle
747  remove_initial_space_and_back_input();
748  if (w && cur_cmd_chr.cmd != par_cmd) back_input(hash_table.noindent_token);
749  }
750 }

784 // Toplevel function. Reads and translates a formula.
785 // Argument as in start_scan_math
786 void Parser::T_math(subtypes type) {
787  auto nm = eqtb_int_table[nomath_code].val;
788  cmi.reset(nm == -3);
789  Trace.reset();
790  trace_needs_space = false;
791  Math &u1 = math_data.get_list(0);
792  bool is_inline = start_scan_math(u1, type);
793  cmi.set_type(is_inline);
794  cmi.check_for_eqnum(type, eqtb_int_table[multimlabel_code].val != 0);
795  if (type == nomathenv_code || type == math_code || type == displaymath_code) {
796  size_t position = is_inline ? everymath_code : everydisplay_code;
797  TokenList everymath = toks_registers[position].val;
798  if (!everymath.empty()) {
799  if (tracing_commands())
800  the_log << lg_startbrace << (is_inline ? "<everymath> " : "<everydisplay> ") << everymath << lg_endbrace;
801  back_input(everymath);
802  }
803  }
804  select_math_font();
805  scan_math3(0, math_data.get_list(0).get_type(), 0);
806  if (tracing_math()) {
807  the_log << lg_start << "Math: " << Trace << lg_end << lg_flush;
808  Trace.reset();
809  math_data.get_list(0).print();
810  the_log << lg_start << Trace << lg_flush;
811  }
812  // Test for the no-mathml mode
813  math_data.realloc_list0();
814  int loc_of_cp = 0;
815  if (nm < 0) {
816  loc_of_cp = math_data.get_list(0).duplicate(true);
817  if (nm != -3) {
818  finish_no_mathml(is_inline, loc_of_cp);
819  return;
820  }
821  }
822  Xml * alter = nullptr;
823  std::string textype = math_data.get_list(0).get_name();
824  if (nm == -3) {
825  Math &w = math_data.get_list(loc_of_cp);
826  alter = w.convert_math_noML(false);
827  alter->change_id(cmi.get_tid());
828  }
829  loc_of_cp = math_data.get_list(0).duplicate(false);
830  Math &u = math_data.get_list(loc_of_cp);
831  // Translate the formula into res
832  Xml *res = nullptr;
833  if ((math_env_props(type) & 8) == 0) u.set_type(math_open_cd);
834  if (u.has_type(math_env_cd)) {
835  res = u.M_array(cmi.get_eqnum_status() == 2, is_inline ? ms_T : ms_D);
836  } else {
837  u.remove_spaces();
838  if (is_inline) {
839  auto k = eqtb_int_table[notrivialmath_code].val;
840  res = u.trivial_math(k);
841  if (res != nullptr) {
842  finish_trivial_math(res);
843  return;
844  }
845  }
846  res = u.convert_math(is_inline ? ms_T : ms_D);
847  }
848  after_math(is_inline);
849  // Insert the result in the tree.
850  Xml *x = new Xml(cst_math, nullptr);
851  x->change_id(cmi.get_mid());
852  x->add_att(cst_xmlns, cst_mathml);
853  x->add_tmp(res);
854  if (!is_inline) x->add_att(cst_mode, cst_display);
855  Xml *res1 = new Xml(np_formula, x);
856  if (alter != nullptr) res1->push_back(alter);
857 
858  res1->change_id(cmi.get_fid());
859  res1->add_att(np_type, cmi.get_pos_att());
860  if (!textype.empty()) res1->add_att(Istring(np_textype), Istring(textype));
861  if (cmi.has_label()) add_math_label(res1);
862  if (the_main->interactive_math) {
863  if (only_input_data)
864  std::cout << x << "\n";
865  else
866  std::cout << res1 << "\n";
867  }
868  the_stack.add_last(res1);
869  if (!is_inline) the_stack.add_nl();
870 }

875 // x is index of result, t is type of math list,
876 // m is 0 for outer math, 1 normally, 2 in \hbox
877 void Parser::scan_math3(int x, math_list_type t, int m) {
878  Token xfct_caller = fct_caller;
879  fct_caller = hash_table.relax_token;
880  mode om = the_stack.get_mode();
881  if (t == math_open_cd) {
882  } // do not change the mode
883  else if (m == 2)
884  the_stack.set_h_mode();
885  else
886  the_stack.set_m_mode();
887  boundary_type aux = bt_math;
888  {
889  Math &u = math_data.get_list(x);
890  if ((math_env_props(u.get_sname()) & 8) != 0)
891  aux = bt_cell;
892  else if (t == math_open_cd)
893  aux = bt_brace;
894  }
895  push_level(aux);
896  if (m == 0 && cmi.get_eqnum_status() == 3) refstepcounter("equation", false);
897  scan_math(x, t);
898  if (m == 0 && (cmi.get_eqnum_status() == 2 || cmi.get_eqnum_status() == 1)) {
899  if (!cmi.end_of_row()) {
900  refstepcounter("equation", false);
901  cmi.insert_special_tag(the_parser.eqtb_string_table[0].val);
902  }
903  if (tracing_math()) cmi.dump_labels();
904  cmi.ml_check_labels();
905  }
906  pop_level(aux);
907  the_stack.set_mode(om);
908  fct_caller = xfct_caller;
909 }

927 // Reads a new token.
928 // Return 0 if end-of data, 1 if token should be ignored, 2 otherwise
929 auto Parser::scan_math1(int res) -> int {
930  get_x_token();
931  if (cur_tok.is_invalid()) {
932  parse_error("End of input reached");
933  return 0;
934  }
935  symcodes T = cur_cmd_chr.cmd;
936  if (T == nobreakspace_cmd) {
937  back_input(Token(other_t_offset, '~'));
938  return 1;
939  }
940  // replace \{ by \lbrace
941  if (T == cst1_cmd && cur_cmd_chr.chr == rbrace_chr) {
942  back_input(hash_table.rbrace_token);
943  return 1;
944  }
945  if (T == cst1_cmd && cur_cmd_chr.chr == lbrace_chr) {
946  back_input(hash_table.lbrace_token);
947  return 1;
948  }
949  if (T == 3) { // dollar sign hack a bit this
950  if (cmi.has_tag()) {
951  back_input(Token(dollar_t_offset, '$'));
952  cmi.handle_tags();
953  return 1;
954  }
955  }
956  if (T == 11 || T == 12 || T == char_given_cmd) {
957  // FIXME what is the purpose of this math mode test
958  if (the_stack.get_mode() == mode_math) {
959  auto c = cur_cmd_chr.chr;
960  if (c > 0 && c < nb_characters) {
961  auto u = eqtb_int_table[c + math_code_offset].val;
962  if (u == 32768) {
963  cur_tok.active_char(c);
964  back_input();
965  return 1;
966  }
967  }
968  }
969  }
970  if (is_m_font(T)) {
971  if (eqtb_int_table[nomath_code].val == -2) {
972  math_data.push_back(res, cur_cmd_chr, subtypes(cur_tok.val));
973  return 1;
974  }
975  math_data.push_back(res, CmdChr(nomath_cmd, one_code), zero_code);
976  math_data.push_back(res, cur_cmd_chr, subtypes(cur_tok.val));
977  TM_fonts();
978  return 1;
979  }
980  add_to_trace(cur_tok);
981  return 2;
982 }

984 // The function that reads a math formula. Read tokens until the end
985 // of the current group is seen. Fills the list number res, of type type
986 void Parser::scan_math(int res, math_list_type type) {
987  for (;;) {
988  int w = scan_math1(res);
989  if (w == 0) return;
990  if (w == 1) continue;
991  symcodes T = cur_cmd_chr.cmd;
992  subtypes c = cur_cmd_chr.chr;
993  Token t = cur_tok;
994  switch (T) {
995  case 1: // open brace, read a group
996  new_math_list(res, math_open_cd, nomathenv_code);
997  continue;
998  case 2: // close brace, end group
999  if (type == math_open_cd || type == math_argument_cd || type == math_hbox_cd) return;
1000  parse_error("Unexpected }");
1001  return;
1002  case 3: // dollar, open or close ?
1003  if (scan_math_dollar(res, type)) return;
1004  continue;
1005  case par_cmd:
1006  err_buf << bf_reset << "Unexpected \\par";
1007  if (type == math_argument_cd) err_buf << " while scanning argument of " << fct_caller.tok_to_str();
1008  signal_error(err_tok, "Unexpected par");
1009  return;
1010  case eqno_cmd: scan_eqno(type); continue;
1011  case tag_cmd: scan_math_tag(c); continue;
1012  case label_cmd:
1013  if (c == 1) { // anchor
1014  remove_initial_star();
1015  sT_optarg_nopar();
1016  parse_error("Illegal anchor in math mode");
1017  continue;
1018  } else if (c == 2) { // anchorlabel
1019  bool h;
1020  std::string s = scan_anchor(h);
1021  std::string a = special_next_arg();
1022  if (h) {
1023  c = mathlabel_code;
1024  TokenList L = token_ns::string_to_list(a, true);
1025  // brace_me(L);
1026  back_input(L);
1027  TokenList L1 = token_ns::string_to_list(s, true);
1028  // brace_me(L1);
1029  back_input(L1);
1030  math_list_type cc = sub_to_math(c);
1031  Token ct = cur_tok;
1032  subtypes k = math_data.find_math_location(cc, nomathenv_code);
1033  CmdChr W = CmdChr(special_math_cmd, k);
1034  math_data.set_type(k, cc);
1035  subtypes r1 = math_argument(0, ct); // should be s
1036  subtypes r2 = math_argument(0, ct); // should be a
1037  Math & u = math_data.get_list(k);
1038  u.push_back_list(r1, math_argument_cd);
1039  u.push_back_list(r2, math_argument_cd);
1040  math_data.push_back(res, W, subtypes(u.get_type()));
1041  } else {
1042  the_tag = s;
1043  cmi.new_label(a, true);
1044  }
1045  continue; // case anchorlabel ??
1046  }
1047  {
1048  std::string s = special_next_arg();
1049  cmi.new_label(s, false);
1050  }
1051  continue;
1052  case ensuremath_cmd: E_all_of_one(t, zero_code); continue;
1053  case begingroup_cmd:
1054  if (c == 0)
1055  push_level(bt_semisimple);
1056  else
1057  pop_level(bt_semisimple);
1058  continue;
1059  case begin_cmd:
1060  case end_cmd:
1061  if (scan_math_env(res, type)) return;
1062  continue;
1063  case left_cmd: {
1064  del_pos k = math_lr_value();
1065  int tmp = new_math_list(res, math_LR_cd, nomathenv_code);
1066  Math & ww = math_data.get_list(tmp);
1067  ww.push_front(CmdChr(T, subtypes(k)), zero_code);
1068  if (ww.back().get_cmd() != right_cmd) {
1069  parse_error("Missing \\right. inserted");
1070  ww.push_back(CmdChr(right_cmd, subtypes(del_dot)), zero_code);
1071  }
1072  continue;
1073  }
1074  case right_cmd: {
1075  del_pos k = math_lr_value();
1076  if (type == math_LR_cd) {
1077  math_data.get_list(res).push_back(CmdChr(right_cmd, subtypes(k)));
1078  return;
1079  }
1080  parse_error("Unexpected \\right");
1081  continue;
1082  }
1083  case special_math_cmd: interpret_math_cmd(res, c); continue;
1084  case multicolumn_cmd: interpret_math_cmd(res, multicolumn_code); continue;
1085  case specmath_cmd: // Tralics commands like \mathmi
1086  interpret_math_cmd(res, c);
1087  continue;
1088  case make_box_cmd:
1089  if (c == hbox_code)
1090  scan_math_hbox(res, hbox_S_code);
1091  else
1092  math_data.push_back(res, cur_cmd_chr, subtypes(cur_tok.val));
1093  continue;
1094  case fbox_cmd:
1095  if (c == fbox_code)
1096  scan_math_hbox(res, fbox_S_code);
1097  else
1098  math_data.push_back(res, cur_cmd_chr, subtypes(cur_tok.val));
1099  continue;
1100  case box_cmd:
1101  if (c == text_code)
1102  scan_hbox(res, text_S_code);
1103  else
1104  scan_hbox(res, mbox_S_code); // what if it is makebox ? [FIXME]
1105  continue;
1106  case alignment_catcode: // case & and \\ in a table
1107  case backslash_cmd:
1108  if (stack_math_in_cell()) {
1109  if (scan_math_endcell(t)) return;
1110 
1111  continue;
1112  }
1113  scan_math_endcell_ok(res);
1114  continue;
1115  case mathfont_cmd:
1116  math_data.push_back(res, cur_cmd_chr, subtypes(cur_tok.val));
1117  word_define(math_font_pos, c, false);
1118  continue;
1119  case undef_cmd: undefined_mac(); continue;
1120  case mathrel_cmd: scan_math_rel(c, res); continue;
1121  case unimp_cmd: T_unimp(c); continue;
1122  case specimp_cmd:
1123  if (c == allowbreak_code) continue;
1124  T_specimp(c);
1125  continue;
1126  case kern_cmd:
1127  case scan_glue_cmd:
1128  case hspace_cmd: {
1129  ScaledInt val = scan_math_kern(T, c);
1130  CmdChr ww = CmdChr(hspace_cmd, c);
1131  math_data.push_back(res, ww, subtypes(val.get_value()));
1132  continue;
1133  }
1134  case start_par_cmd:
1135  // no error ?
1136  continue;
1137  case char_num_cmd: {
1138  auto C = scan_27bit_int();
1139  CmdChr ww = CmdChr(char_given_cmd, subtypes(C));
1140  math_data.push_back(res, ww, subtypes(0));
1141  }
1142  continue;
1143  case char_given_cmd:
1144  case math_given_cmd: math_data.push_back(res, cur_cmd_chr, subtypes(0)); continue;
1145  case relax_cmd: math_data.push_back(res, cur_cmd_chr, subtypes(cur_tok.val)); continue;
1146  case mathord_cmd: // may be bold
1147  {
1148  auto F = subtypes(cur_tok.val);
1149  CmdChr R = cur_cmd_chr;
1150  if (math_loc(c) > first_inline_hack && math_loc(c) < last_inline_bhack && is_pos_par(atmathversion_code))
1151  R = CmdChr(mathordb_cmd, c);
1152  math_data.push_back(res, R, F);
1153  continue;
1154  }
1155  default:
1156  if (T == 12 && c == '\'' && type != math_hbox_cd) {
1157  Trace.remove_last_quote();
1158  scan_prime();
1159  continue;
1160  }
1161  if (T >= first_mode_independent) {
1162  remove_from_trace();
1163  translate01();
1164  continue;
1165  }
1166  if (T < 16 && cur_tok.not_a_cmd()) {
1167  // in the case \let\A=B, we replace \A by B (avoids core dump)
1168  cur_cmd_chr = CmdChr(T, c);
1169  }
1170  if (T < 16) { // Case of a character
1171  auto font = subtypes(eqtb_int_table[math_font_pos].val);
1172  math_data.push_back(res, cur_cmd_chr, font);
1173  } else
1174  math_data.push_back(res, cur_cmd_chr, subtypes(cur_tok.val));
1175  }
1176  }
1177 }

1257 // true if no equation number has to be produced
1258 // leaves a hole for the label
1259 auto MathHelper::end_of_row() -> bool {
1260  auto k = last_ml_pos;
1261  auto n = multi_labels.size();
1262  bool sseen_label = false;
1263  bool seen_notag = false;
1264  bool seen_tag = false;
1265  for (size_t i = k; i < n; i++) {
1266  int v = multi_labels_type[i];
1267  if (v == 0) continue; // boundary
1268  if (v == 1) { // a label
1269  if (sseen_label) { multi_labels_type[i] = -v; }
1270  sseen_label = true;
1271  } else if (v == 2 || v == 3) { // a tag
1272  if (seen_tag) { multi_labels_type[i] = -v; }
1273  seen_tag = true;
1274  } else if (v == 4)
1275  seen_notag = true;
1276  }
1277  bool ok = seen_tag || seen_notag;
1278  if (seen_notag && sseen_label && !seen_tag) ok = false; // ??
1279  if (!ok) new_multi_label("", 5);
1280  new_multi_label("", 0); // add a new boundary
1281  last_ml_pos = multi_labels.size();
1282  return ok;
1283 }

1360 // We have seen \begin or \end
1361 // return false if parsing continues, true otherwise (case of \end)
1362 auto Parser::scan_math_env(int res, math_list_type type) -> bool {
1363  symcodes T = cur_cmd_chr.cmd;
1364  bool at_start = T == begin_cmd;
1365  // Check if v-part of template has to be inserted here
1366  if (!at_start && stack_math_in_cell()) {
1367  if (the_stack.is_frame(np_cell) && !the_stack.is_omit_cell()) {
1368  TokenList L = the_stack.get_u_or_v(false);
1369  if (!L.empty()) {
1370  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startbrace << "template v-part " << L << lg_endbrace;
1371  back_input(cur_tok);
1372  back_input(L);
1373  the_stack.mark_omit_cell();
1374  return false;
1375  }
1376  }
1377  }
1378  cmi.update_all_env_ctr(at_start);
1379  std::string s = fetch_name0();
1380  add_to_trace(s);
1381  Token eenv = find_env_token(s, false); // \endfoo
1382  CmdChr end_val = cur_cmd_chr; // value of \endfoo
1383  Token benv = find_env_token(s, true); // \foo
1384  if (end_val.is_user()) { // user defined env, expand
1385  if (at_start) {
1386  back_input(benv);
1387  back_input(hash_table.OB_token); // Insert OB
1388  cmi.update_math_env_ctr(true);
1389  } else { // end something
1390  if (cmi.get_math_env_ctr() > 0) {
1391  back_input(hash_table.CB_token); // matches the OB above
1392  cmi.update_math_env_ctr(false);
1393  back_input(eenv);
1394  } else {
1395  // FIXME
1396  T_end(s);
1397  return false;
1398  }
1399  }
1400  return false;
1401  }
1402  // non-user env
1403  subtypes et = nomathenv_code;
1404  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == math_env_cmd) et = cur_cmd_chr.chr;
1405  if (at_start) {
1406  if (et == nomathenv_code || ((math_env_props(et) & 1) != 0)) {
1407  Buffer &B = math_buffer;
1408  B << bf_reset << "Illegal \\begin{" << s << "} found in math mode";
1409  parse_error(err_tok, B.c_str(), "bad env");
1410  }
1411  if ((math_env_props(et) & 16) != 0) ignore_optarg();
1412  new_math_list(res, math_env_cd, et);
1413  return false;
1414  }
1415  // Case \end{foo}
1416  bool at_level_zero = cmi.get_all_env_ctr() == -1;
1417  if (at_level_zero && cmi.has_tag()) {
1418  TokenList L = token_ns::string_to_list(s, true);
1419  back_input(L);
1420  back_input(hash_table.end_token);
1421  cmi.handle_tags();
1422  return false;
1423  }
1424  if (type == math_env_cd && et == math_data.get_list(res).get_sname()) {
1425  if (res == 0) { // end of main formula
1426  if (cmi.get_eqnum_status() > 1) the_tag = the_parser.eqtb_string_table[0].val;
1427  }
1428  return true;
1429  }
1430  {
1431  Buffer &B = math_buffer;
1432  B << bf_reset << "Bad \\end{" << s << "}; expected ";
1433  if (type == math_env_cd)
1434  B << "\\end{" << math_data.get_list(res).get_name() << "}";
1435  else if (type == math_dollar_cd)
1436  B << "$";
1437  else if (type == math_ddollar_cd)
1438  B << "$$";
1439  else if (type == math_LR_cd)
1440  B << "\\right";
1441  else
1442  B << "}";
1443  parse_error(err_tok, B.to_string(), "bad end");
1444  }
1445  return true;
1446 }

1448 // We have seen a dollar sign, expected closing delimiter type
1449 // Returns true if Ok, false if parsing continues
1450 auto Parser::scan_math_dollar(int res, math_list_type type) -> bool {
1451  switch (type) {
1452  case math_dollar_cd: return true;
1453  case math_ddollar_cd: // We want $$ or equivalent
1454  get_x_token();
1455  add_to_trace(cur_tok);
1456  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd != 3) parse_error("Display math should end with $$");
1457  return true;
1458  case math_open_cd:
1459  if (!the_stack.in_h_mode()) {
1460  parse_error(err_tok, "Out of scope $ ignored, maybe a } is missing here", "extra $");
1461  return false;
1462  }
1463  // fall through
1464  case math_hbox_cd: {
1465  // it's a math formula inside a formula
1466  TokenList everymath = toks_registers[everymath_code].val;
1467  if (!everymath.empty()) {
1468  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startbrace << "<everymath> " << everymath << lg_endbrace;
1469  back_input(everymath);
1470  }
1471  select_math_font();
1472  new_math_list(res, math_dollar_cd, nomathenv_code);
1473  return false;
1474  }
1475  case math_LR_cd:
1476  back_input();
1477  parse_error(err_tok, "Missing \\right. inserted", "missing \\right");
1478  math_data.get_list(res).push_back(CmdChr(right_cmd, subtypes(del_dot)));
1479  return true;
1480  case math_argument_cd: parse_error(err_tok, "Extra $ ignored while scanning argument of ", fct_caller, "", "extra $"); return false;
1481  default: parse_error("Extra $ ignored..."); return false;
1482  }
1483 }

1485 // We have seen \tag, \@xtag o<r \@ytag
1486 // 0: \tag, 1=\@xtag 2=\@ytag 3=\notag 4=\nonumber
1487 void Parser::scan_math_tag(subtypes c) {
1488  if (c == 3 || c == 4) {
1489  if (cmi.get_eqnum_status() == 2 || cmi.get_eqnum_status() == 1) {
1490  cmi.new_multi_label("", 4);
1491  } else if (cmi.get_eqnum_status() == 0) {
1492  parse_error("Illegal \\notag");
1493  } else { // decrement equation number
1494  auto v = eqtb_int_table[equation_ctr_pos].val;
1495  word_define(equation_ctr_pos, v - 1, true);
1496  }
1497  return;
1498  }
1499  bool is_star = false;
1500  if (c == 0) is_star = remove_initial_star();
1501  TokenList L = read_arg();
1502  if (c == 0 && (cmi.get_eqnum_status() == 2 || cmi.get_eqnum_status() == 1)) {
1503  L.remove_if([](const Token &m) { return m.is_math_shift(); });
1504  L.push_front(hash_table.relax_token);
1505  L.push_front(hash_table.ref_token);
1506  L.push_front(hash_table.let_token);
1507  brace_me(L);
1508  std::string val = sT_translate(L);
1509  cmi.new_multi_label(val, (is_star ? 3 : 2));
1510  return;
1511  }
1512  if (c == 0 && (cmi.get_eqnum_status() == 0)) {
1513  parse_error("Illegal \\tag");
1514  return;
1515  }
1516  if (c == 0) {
1517  brace_me(L);
1518  L.remove_if([](const Token &m) { return m.is_math_shift(); });
1519  L.push_front(is_star ? hash_table.ytag_token : hash_table.xtag_token);
1520  back_input(L);
1521  } else {
1522  if (c == 2) cmi.starred_tag();
1523  cmi.add_tag(L);
1524  }
1525 }

1702  dmres = to_signed(the_main->SH.hash_find());
1703  }
1704  Token m = scan_style();
1705  add_to_trace(m);
1706  subtypes r1 = math_argument(0, ct);
1707  subtypes r2 = math_argument(0, ct);
1708  Math & u = math_data.get_list(k);
1709  u.push_back(CmdChr(left_cmd, subtypes(k1)), zero_code);
1710  u.push_back(CmdChr(right_cmd, subtypes(k2)), zero_code);
1711  u.push_back(CmdChr(right_cmd, subtypes(dmres)), zero_code);
1712 
1713  token_from_list(m);
1714  cur_tok = m;
1715  u.push_back(cur_cmd_chr, subtypes(cur_tok.val));
1716  u.push_back_list(r1, math_argument_cd);
1717  u.push_back_list(r2, math_argument_cd);
1718  math_data.push_back(res, W, subtypes(u.get_type()));
1719 }

1721 // Handles \mathmi[foo][bar][a][b]{etc} and friends
1722 void Parser::scan_math_mi(int res, subtypes c, subtypes k, CmdChr W) {
1723  Token ct = cur_tok;
1724  std::string s;
1725  if (c == mathbox_code) {
1726  s = group_to_string(); // name of the env (no expand here ?)
1727  add_to_trace(s);
1728  }
1729  std::vector<MathElt> T; // the optional arguments
1730  for (;;) {
1731  remove_initial_space_and_back_input();
1732  if (!cur_tok.is_open_bracket()) break;
1733  TokenList L;
1734  read_optarg_nopar(L);
1735  brace_me(L);
1736  back_input(L);
1737  subtypes r1 = math_argument(0, ct);
1738  T.emplace_back(CmdChr(math_list_cmd, r1), subtypes(math_argument_cd));
1739  }
1740  auto n = T.size();
1741  n = n / 2;
1742  n = n + n; // Ignore last if odd
1743  subtypes r1 = math_argument(0, ct);
1744  Math & u = math_data.get_list(k);
1745  if (c == mathbox_code) {
1746  auto ss = Istring(s);
1747  u.set_name(subtypes(ss.value));
1748  }
1749  u.push_back_list(r1, math_argument_cd);
1750  for (size_t i = 0; i < n; i++) u.push_back(T[i]);
1751  math_data.push_back(res, W, subtypes(u.get_type()));
1752 }

1777 // Scans a command with some arguments.
1778 void Parser::interpret_math_cmd(int res, subtypes c) {
1779  Token ct = cur_tok;
1780  subtypes k = math_data.find_math_location(sub_to_math(c), nomathenv_code);
1781  CmdChr W = CmdChr(special_math_cmd, k);
1782  switch (c) {
1783  case genfrac_code: interpret_genfrac_cmd(res, k, W); return;
1784  case mathchoice_code: interpret_mathchoice_cmd(res, k, W); return;
1785  case sqrt_code:
1786  remove_initial_space_and_back_input();
1787  if (cur_tok.is_open_bracket()) {
1788  c = root_code;
1789  opt_to_mandatory();
1790  }
1791  break;
1792  case xleftarrow_code:
1793  case xrightarrow_code: opt_to_mandatory(); break;
1794  case smash_code:
1795  case cfrac_code: opt_to_mandatory(); break;
1796  case mathmi_code:
1797  case mathmo_code:
1798  case mathmn_code:
1799  case mathnothing_code:
1800  case mathci_code:
1801  case mathcn_code:
1802  case mathcsymbol_code:
1803  case multiscripts_code:
1804  case mathbox_code: scan_math_mi(res, c, k, W); return;
1805  case operatorname_code:
1806  if (remove_initial_star()) c = operatornamestar_code;
1807  break;
1808  default:; // nothing special
1809  }
1810  math_data.set_type(k, sub_to_math(c)); // may be needed in some cases
1811  // bool is_math_accent = c>=first_maccent_code && c<=last_maccent_code;
1812  // int first_spec = is_math_accent?1:0;
1813  // if(c==sqrt_code) first_spec = 1;
1814  // subtypes r1 = math_argument(first_spec,ct);
1815  subtypes r1 = math_argument(0, ct);
1816  subtypes r2 = zero_code;
1817  subtypes r3 = zero_code;
1818  if (c == cfrac_code || c == qopname_code || c == multicolumn_code) {
1819  r2 = math_argument(0, ct);
1820  r3 = math_argument(0, ct);
1821  } else if (c <= last_marg_code || c > last_maccent_code)
1822  r2 = math_argument(0, ct);
1823  else if (c == xleftarrow_code || c == xrightarrow_code || c == smash_code)
1824  r2 = math_argument(0, ct);
1825  Math &u = math_data.get_list(k);
1826  u.push_back_list(r1, math_argument_cd);
1827  if (r2 != 0U) u.push_back_list(r2, math_argument_cd);
1828  if (r3 != 0U) u.push_back_list(r3, math_argument_cd);
1829  math_data.push_back(res, W, subtypes(u.get_type()));
1830 }

1894 // Converts a cell. Updates n, the index of the cell in the row.
1895 auto Math::convert_cell(size_t &n, std::vector<AttList> &table, math_style W) -> Xml * {
1896  Xml *res = new Xml(cst_mtd, nullptr);
1897  if (empty()) {
1898  n++; // empty cell, no atts needed.
1899  return res;
1900  }
1901  Xid id = res->get_id();
1902  int tbl_align = 0;
1903  cmi.set_cid(id);
1904  Math args = *this;
1905  if (!(front().get_cmd() == special_math_cmd && front().get_lcmd() == sub_to_math(multicolumn_code))) {
1906  auto m = table.size();
1907  if (n < m) id.add_attribute(table[n], true);
1908  n++;
1909  } else {
1910  Math L = front().get_list();
1911  pop_front();
1912  skip_initial_space();
1913  if (!empty()) the_parser.parse_error(the_parser.err_tok, "Cell contains garbage after \\multicolumn", "multicol garbage");
1914  L.get_arg1().convert_this_to_string(math_buffer); // get the span
1915  int k = atoi(math_buffer.c_str());
1916  if (k <= 0)
1917  n++;
1918  else {
1919  id.add_attribute(np_columnspan, Istring(the_main->SH.find(k)));
1920  n += to_unsigned(k);
1921  }
1922  L.get_arg2().convert_this_to_string(math_buffer);
1923  char c = math_buffer.single_char();
1924  if (c == 'l') tbl_align = 1;
1925  if (c == 'r') tbl_align = 2;
1926  args = L.get_arg3();
1927  }
1928  int k = args.check_align();
1929  if (k != 0) tbl_align = k;
1930  if (tbl_align == 1)
1931  id.add_attribute(np_columnalign, np_left);
1932  else if (tbl_align == 2)
1933  id.add_attribute(np_columnalign, np_right);
1934  else if (tbl_align == 3)
1935  id.add_attribute(np_columnalign, np_center);
1936  Xml *tmp = args.convert_math(W);
1937  res->add_tmp(tmp);
1938  return res;
1939 }

1941 // Converts an array.
1942 auto Math::split_as_array(std::vector<AttList> &table, math_style W, bool numbered) -> Xml * {
1943  Math cell;
1944  bool is_multline = sname == multline_code || sname == multline_star_code;
1945  bool needs_dp = (math_env_props(sname) & 1) != 0;
1946  if (sname == aligned_code) needs_dp = true; // OK FIXME
1947  if (sname == split_code) needs_dp = true; // OK FIXME
1948  size_t n = 0; // index of cell in row.
1949  Xml * res = new Xml(cst_mtable, nullptr);
1950  Xml * row = new Xml(cst_mtr, nullptr);
1951  Xid rid = cmi.get_rid(); // old rid, to be restored at the end
1952  Xid cid = cmi.get_cid();
1953  Xid taid = cmi.get_taid();
1954  cmi.set_taid(res->get_id());
1955  cmi.set_rid(row->get_id());
1956  if (needs_dp) W = ms_D;
1957  res->push_back(row);
1958  bool first_cell = is_multline;
1959  if (numbered) cmi.reset_last_ml_pos();
1960  while (!empty()) {
1961  symcodes cmd = front().get_cmd();
1962  if (cmd == alignment_catcode) { // finish cell
1963  pop_front();
1964  row->push_back(cell.convert_cell(n, table, W));
1965  cmi.set_cid(cid);
1966  cell.clear();
1967  first_cell = false;
1968  } else if (cmd == backslash_cmd) { // finish row and cell
1969  pop_front();
1970  remove_opt_arg(true); // optional argument ignored.
1971  row->push_back(cell.convert_cell(n, table, W));
1972  if (first_cell) cmi.get_cid().add_attribute(np_columnalign, np_left);
1973  cmi.set_cid(cid);
1974  cell.clear();
1975  first_cell = false;
1976  if (numbered) cmi.ml_second_pass(row, the_parser.tracing_math());
1977 
1978  n = 0;
1979  row = new Xml(cst_mtr, nullptr);
1980  cmi.set_rid(row->get_id());
1981  res->push_back(row);
1982  } else if (cmd == space_catcode && cell.empty()) {
1983  pop_front();
1984  } else {
1985  cell.push_back(front());
1986  pop_front();
1987  }
1988  }
1989  if (!cell.empty()) {
1990  row->push_back(cell.convert_cell(n, table, W));
1991  if (is_multline) cmi.get_cid().add_attribute(np_columnalign, np_right);
1992  cmi.set_cid(cid);
1993  }
1994  if (row->size() == 0) // kill the last empty row
1995  res->pop_back();
1996  else {
1997  if (numbered) cmi.ml_second_pass(row, the_parser.tracing_math());
1998  }
1999 
2000  Xid w = the_main->the_stack->next_xid(res);
2001  w.add_attribute(cmi.get_taid()); // move the attributes
2002  cmi.set_rid(rid);
2003  cmi.set_taid(taid);
2004  res->change_id(w);
2005  if (needs_dp) res->add_att(cst_displaystyle, np_true);
2006  return res;
2007 }

2051 // We assume here that the formula has two tokens. The first is underscore
2052 // or caret, code in cmd. In the case of $_x$ or $_{x}$ or $^{y}$
2053 // return a non-mathml expression in case the argument is OK.
2054 auto Math::trivial_math_index(symcodes cmd) -> Xml * {
2055  Buffer &B = math_buffer;
2056  B.reset();
2057  auto L = value.begin();
2058  ++L;
2059  name_positions loc = cmd == underscore_catcode ? np_s_sub : np_s_sup;
2060  CmdChr w = L->get_cmd_chr();
2061  bool have_font = false;
2062  name_positions font_pos = cst_empty;
2063  if (w.is_letter() || w.is_other())
2064  B.push_back(w.char_val());
2065  else if (L->is_list()) {
2066  const Math &A = L->get_list();
2067  auto C = A.value.begin();
2068  auto E = A.value.end();
2069  if (C == E) return nullptr;
2070  if (C->get_cmd() == mathfont_cmd) {
2071  have_font = true;
2072  subtypes s = C->get_chr();
2073  if (s == math_f_italic)
2074  font_pos = np_font_it;
2075  else if (s == math_f_upright)
2076  have_font = false;
2077  else if (s == math_f_sansserif)
2078  font_pos = np_font_sansserif;
2079  else if (s == math_f_monospace)
2080  font_pos = np_font_tt;
2081  else if (s == math_f_bold)
2082  font_pos = np_font_bold;
2083  else
2084  return nullptr;
2085  ++C;
2086  }
2087  while (C != E) {
2088  if (C->is_char())
2089  B.push_back(C->get_char());
2090  else if (C->get_cmd() == mathfont_cmd) {
2091  ++C;
2092  if (C == E) break;
2093  return nullptr;
2094  } else
2095  return nullptr;
2096  ++C;
2097  }
2098  } else
2099  return nullptr;
2100  Xml *tmp = Stack::fonts1(loc);
2101  Xml *xval = new Xml(Istring(B));
2102  if (have_font) {
2103  Xml *tmp2 = Stack::fonts1(font_pos);
2104  tmp2->push_back(xval);
2105  xval = tmp2;
2106  }
2107  tmp->push_back(xval);
2108  return tmp;
2109 }

2118 // Only digits can appear before the hat. Only one token (or a list)
2119 // can appear after the hat. This should be e, o or a special exponent.
2120 // The result is as if you said: 1\textsuperscript{er} (without $).

2126 auto Math::trivial_math(long action) -> Xml * {
2127  action = action % 8;
2128  if (action == 0) return nullptr;
2129  auto L = value.begin();
2130  if (L == value.end()) return nullptr; // empty formula is never trivial
2131  int len = 1;
2132  ++L;
2133  if (L != value.end()) {
2134  ++L;
2135  len = 2;
2136  if (L != value.end()) len = 3;
2137  }
2138  symcodes cmd = front().get_cmd();
2139  Xml * res = nullptr;
2140  if (((action & 4) != 0) && len == 2 && (cmd == underscore_catcode || cmd == hat_catcode)) res = trivial_math_index(cmd);
2141  if (res != nullptr) return res;
2142  if ((action & 1) != 0) res = special1();
2143  if (res != nullptr) return res;
2144  if (len != 1) return nullptr;
2145  if ((action & 2) == 0) return nullptr;
2146  if (front().is_digit()) {
2147  Istring sval = the_names[cst_dig0 + front().val_as_digit()];
2148  return new Xml(sval);
2149  }
2150  if (front().is_letter_token()) {
2151  auto c = front().get_char().value;
2152  if (c < nb_simplemath) return math_data.get_simplemath_val(to_signed(c));
2153  }
2154  if (front().is_other_token() && front().get_char() == '-') return new Xml(Istring("&#x2013;"));
2155  if (front().get_cmd() == mathord_cmd || front().get_cmd() == mathordb_cmd || front().get_cmd() == mathbin_cmd ||
2156  front().get_cmd() == mathop_cmd || front().get_cmd() == mathopn_cmd || front().get_cmd() == mathrel_cmd ||
2157  front().get_cmd() == mathinner_cmd || front().get_cmd() == mathbetween_cmd || front().get_cmd() == mathopen_cmd ||
2158  front().get_cmd() == mathclose_cmd) {
2159  int c = front().get_chr();
2160  if (first_inline_hack <= c && c <= last_inline_hack) return math_ns::get_builtin_alt(c);
2161  }
2162  return nullptr;
2163 }

2295 // Return 1 if the list is left aligned, 2 if right aligned, 0 if centered
